'dictionary map' might be confusing because the dictionary refers to the entire set of components, rather than a single of them.

I know that this is not part of your PR, but I should we should replace 'izip', that we are importing from a private module (bad, bad), with 'zip', which does almost the same thing and is a builtin (ie doesn't have to be imported).
I would be inclined to think that initializing a class instance does imply that its parameters/variable are also initialized. Thus "and parameters" might perhaps be confusing to some.
